# koku-ui on-prem dev server

## Default interpretation

When the user says **dev server**, **dev-server**, **start the UI locally**, or similar **without naming another app**, they mean **`submodules/koku-ui`** — the on-prem Cost Management host plus federated remotes (HCCM, ROS, Sources, RBAC).

## Preferred command

From **`submodules/koku-ui`** (after `git submodule update --init vendor/insights-rbac-ui` if needed):

```bash
npm run start:onprem:dev
```

This runs [`scripts/setup-onprem-env.sh`](../../submodules/koku-ui/scripts/setup-onprem-env.sh) (requires `oc` logged into a cluster with cost-onprem), then [`start:onprem`](../../submodules/koku-ui/package.json) via `concurrently`. Default URL: **http://localhost:9001/**.

## Do not use by default

| Command | When |
| ------- | ---- |
| `npm run start:onprem` alone | Missing `API_PROXY_URL` — host webpack fails. Only if the user explicitly wants bare `start:onprem` or env is already set. |
| `npm run start:onprem:koku` | Local Koku API only — use only when the user asks for local Koku, not cluster-backed dev. |
| `npm run start:onprem -w @koku-ui/rbac-ui-onprem` | RBAC webpack watch only — not the full stack unless the user asks for RBAC in isolation. |

## Before starting

1. Confirm working directory is `submodules/koku-ui`.
2. If the user needs cluster proxy/Keycloak vars, use **`start:onprem:dev`** — do not invent `API_PROXY_URL` unless they choose the local-Koku path.
3. Run in a **background terminal** when automating; report host URL and `/rbac/plugin-manifest.json` as a quick health check when the stack is up.

